==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foliate
<hw>Fo"li*ate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>foliatus</ets> leaved, leafy, fr. <ets>folium</ets> leaf. See
<er>Foliage</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Furnished with leaves;
leafy; as, a <xex>foliate</xex> stalk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Foliate curve</b></col>. <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <cd>Same as
<er>Folium</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foliate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Foliate
<hw>Fo"li*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Foliated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Foliating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To beat into a leaf, or thin plate.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To spread over with a thin coat of tin and
quicksilver; <as>as, to <ex>foliate</ex> a looking-glass</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foliated</ent>⟦br⟧
